Appendix 2 — Aerostack Scoring Rubric (Role-agnostic, build-ready)

Shared rules for all categories
	•	Exactly one Outcome Owner; ≤3 Merited Contributors (25–50% each).
	•	Effort (1–5) and Outcome (1–5) are chosen from the buckets below (no half steps).
	•	Loop Score = Effort × Outcome.
	•	Velocity (90d) = (0–30d avg × 0.5) + (31–60d × 0.3) + (61–90d × 0.2).
	•	Lessons (abstract ≤280 chars + tags + reuse note) required at Adaptation.

Tip: choose the lowest bucket that fully fits the work. When in doubt, round down on Effort, honest on Outcome.

⸻

1) Delivery / Engineering Project (ENG)

Effort (pick one)
	1.	Trivial fix / one-file change
	2.	Small feature / isolated component
	3.	Sprint-sized change w/ dependencies
	4.	Multi-sprint, cross-team, infra/app changes
	5.	Program-scale / multi-service, migrations, net-new platform

Outcome (pick one)
	1.	Missed acceptance/SLO, regressions introduced
	2.	Partial acceptance, notable defects/debt left
	3.	Meets acceptance, stable in prod (no major issues)
	4.	Exceeds NFRs (perf/cost/runtime) with measurable gain
	5.	Step-change: platform leverage, major perf/cost win, unlocks new capability

Secondary metrics (reference only): on-time %, post-release defects, perf/cost deltas.
Velocity tweak: none.

⸻

2) Stewardship / Managed Services (MSP)

Effort
	1.	Routine checks / automation runbooks
	2.	Low-touch multi-asset care (backups/patches)
	3.	Complex recurring cycles across estates (patching, backups, IAM hygiene)
	4.	High-coordination upgrades/compliance waves
	5.	Crisis/migration/major reliability program

Outcome
	1.	SLAs missed; repeat incidents; MTTR trending worse
	2.	SLAs barely met; no improvement trend
	3.	SLAs met; stability maintained; MTTR acceptable
	4.	SLAs exceeded and measurable improvements (cost, perf, risk)
	5.	Material risk/cost reduction; reliability step-change; sustained trend up

Secondary: SLA %, uptime, MTTR/MTTD, cost/perf trend.
Velocity tweak: apply consistency floor option (Velocity ≥ 0.8 × avg_90d) to avoid one bad week nuking score.

⸻

3) Go-To-Market / Marketing (GTM)

Effort
	1.	Single asset update (one-pager, blog, deck tweak)
	2.	Light campaign/enablement (email, social, 1–2 assets)
	3.	Multi-asset, cross-channel campaign; events/webinars
	4.	Program launch (partners/PR/events) with measurement
	5.	Major repositioning/brand system; multi-quarter program

Outcome
	1.	No observable lift (traffic/engagement/pipeline)
	2.	Minor lift; below target KPIs
	3.	Hits KPI targets (MQL/engagement/pipeline influenced)
	4.	Exceeds KPIs; sustained pipeline influence; partner credit
	5.	Category movement / partner tier influence / sustained demand curve up

Secondary: MQL→SQL rates, CAC proxy, partner co-marketing credits.
Velocity tweak: slight recency bias (you’ll naturally get it via the 50/30/20 weighting).

⸻

4) Business Development / Sales (BD)

Effort
	1.	Intro/qualification, discovery notes
	2.	Light proposal / SOW draft
	3.	Full solutioning; multi-stakeholder alignment
	4.	Complex deal (legal/security/finance), tough negotiations
	5.	Multi-party ecosystem deal; partner motions; strategic packaging

Outcome
	1.	No next step; stall/loss
	2.	Stage advance without material value change
	3.	Closed-Won at target scope/margin/terms
	4.	Closed-Won above target (better margin/term quality)
	5.	Strategic win: marquee logo/size/tier unlocks new lanes

Secondary: $ booked, margin/terms quality, CEI credits, partner tier movement.
Velocity tweak: consider materiality buckets operationally (don’t change score math).

