5) Operations / Internal Change

5a) OPS:Finance

Effort
	1.	SOP tweak (reporting template, single metric)
	2.	Team-level process change (AP/AR cadence)
	3.	Cross-team system/process rollout (billing/revenue ops)
	4.	Org-wide policy/system (forecasting, cost controls)
	5.	Structural transformation (unit economics overhaul)

Outcome
	1.	No adoption; data quality declines
	2.	Partial adoption; weak signal
	3.	Adopted; measurable efficiency/margin gains
	4.	Broad adoption; durable gains (error/variance drop)
	5.	Structural step-change (compliance, margin, cash cycle)

Secondary: adoption %, cycle-time, variance/error rate, forecast accuracy.

5b) OPS:HR

Effort
	1.	Policy tweak (PTO template, onboarding checklist)
	2.	Team-level ritual (weekly check-ins, showcases)
	3.	Cross-team cadence/system (reviews, compensation calendar)
	4.	Org policy/system (benefits, compliance, DEI reporting)
	5.	Org transformation (career lattice, leveling, promotion process)

Outcome
	1.	No adoption; confusion/friction up
	2.	Partial adoption; negligible gain
	3.	Adopted; measurable clarity/retention/throughput gains
	4.	Broad adoption; sustained improvements across teams
	5.	Structural shift (attrition ↓, time-to-productive ↓, compliance ↑)

Secondary: time-to-productive, retention %, cycle-times, incident counts.

5c) OPS:SalesOps (maps to RevOps)

Effort
	1.	CRM hygiene tweak; simple dashboard
	2.	Team pipeline process; handoff rules
	3.	Cross-team GTM system; conversion playbooks
	4.	Org-wide forecasting + quota/territory system
	5.	Structural GTM architecture (ICPs, tiers, partner motions)

Outcome
	1.	No pipeline/forecast quality change
	2.	Partial adoption; hygiene up, no conversion gain
	3.	Adopted; conversion or forecast accuracy improves
	4.	Broad adoption; sustained pipeline quality/lift
	5.	Step-change in conversion velocity or forecast accuracy

Secondary: stage conversion %, forecast accuracy, cycle time, pipeline coverage.

Velocity tweak for OPS: reward durability—if adoption backslides within 30–60d, cap Outcome at 3.

